NEW STUDY: "Nearly 20% of low-income people in states that did not expand #Medicaid said they passed up needed medical care in the past 12 months because they couldn’t afford it."

Medicaid is a key part of our #healthcare delivery system.

https://t.co/Xz4Dxevfxx

More than 650,000 people in Washington state have gained coverage through the expansion of #Medicaid coverage.

Medicaid is a key part of our #healthcare delivery system, and we should continue moving toward ways to innovate in Medicaid and save costs.

https://t.co/Xz4Dxevfxx

We lost a trailblazer today.  Paul pushed us to find our better selves to make the world a better place. From a garage in his beloved Northwest, Paul was a disruptive agent of change who revolutionized how we learn, communicate, and interact. https://t.co/kOFP0bHv24

The Tri-Cities area is a vital part of our state's economic engine. I'm so glad to see that Tri-Cities Airport is adding new nonstop service to Los Angeles, which will help us unlock even greater opportunities and more jobs for the region.

I was proud to help write the FAA bill that funded air traffic control towers, including the tower at Walla Walla Regional Airport. Regional airports are a critical economic driver for communities throughout Washington state.

https://t.co/WZs02Infoo

A new report from @USGAO found that “low-income people in states that haven’t expanded Medicaid are much more likely to forgo needed medical care than those in other states.”

The #Medicaid expansion has helped thousands of people in Washington state.

https://t.co/Xz4Dxevfxx

This month, the Senate passed #bipartisan legislation I helped author to fully fund contract air traffic control towers, which will help Walla Walla Regional Airport pay for its air traffic control tower under contract with the #FAA.

https://t.co/WZs02I5EwQ

For the families, people with disabilities, seniors, children, and veterans who use Medicaid for #healthcare, we cannot allow the war on Medicaid to continue.

#Medicaid is a key part of our health care delivery system.

https://t.co/Xz4Dxevfxx

My #FAAreauthorization legislation, which the U.S. Senate passed earlier this month, reforms the #FAA’s Contract Tower Cost Share Program.

This will save the @PortWallaWalla roughly $100,000 per year.

https://t.co/WZs02I5EwQ

Access to #healthcare through the #Medicaid expansion was big in Washington state, especially among rural communities.

Thanks to the expansion, counties like Douglas and Chelan have seen their uninsured rates drop by more than 60%.

https://t.co/Xz4Dxevfxx

Regional airports are a critical economic driver for communities throughout Washington state.

From Walla Walla to Bellingham, ensuring these communities have thriving airports helps grow small businesses and create new jobs.

https://t.co/WZs02Infoo

Honored to have received a 100 score on the @HRC scorecard for my commitment to protecting and advancing the rights of #LGBTQ people. Together we will continue the march towards full equality. #HRCscorecard https://t.co/XYz4sJA4b3

The Trump administration is pushing yet another plan to expand junk insurance that doesn’t cover basics & hurts people with pre-existing conditions.

Americans want more affordable #healthcare with meaningful coverage—not junk plans that don’t protect us.

https://t.co/Rqdpq7sk6V

As I’ve traveled through the state of Washington, law enforcement officers & local communities have told me we need new tools to fight the #opioid epidemic. That’s why I’ve worked with people across our state to try to provide the solutions our law enforcement & communities want.

Last month I met with law enforcement leaders, including @AGOWA Ferguson, @KingCountyWA Undersheriff Somers, @PierceSheriff Pastor & @SnoCoSheriff Trenary, to discuss #bipartisan legislation to fight back against the #opioid epidemic.

Today that bill was signed into law. https://t.co/8ja6xtd6LV
People should not be discriminated against because of their medical history. We must defend the provision of the Affordable Care Act that protects coverage for pre-existing conditions. #ACA

The Affordable Care Act’s pre-existing condition protections are under threat by a federal lawsuit, supported by the Trump administration, that could be decided by the U.S. Supreme Court.

Patients should not be denied access to #healthcare because of a pre-existing condition.

Today, the SUPPORT for Patients & Communities Act was signed into law. It contains more than 70 proposals to help combat the #opioid & heroin epidemic, including important initiatives & priorities I authored & advocated for.

See the full list here: https://t.co/C6OyRFuSF8. https://t.co/gfYcNhebla

From 2016 to 2017, the uninsured rate in Washington state went up by 1.5% following President Trump's deliberate sabotage of the #healthcare system.

We want patients in Washington state to be protected. Denying people insurance is a bad idea.

Legislation signed into law this week includes provisions from my Comprehensive Addiction Reform, Education, and Safety Act to increase penalties on #opioid manufacturers who fail to take reasonable steps to prevent their drugs from entering the black market.

The individual health insurance market is an important source of coverage for Washingtonians. But since President Trump took office, Washington state’s individual health insurance market has seen a 50% hike in approved premium increases. #ProtectOurCare

In Washington state, more than 600,000 people have received #healthcare through #Medicaid Expansion.

In states like ours that have expanded Medicaid, individual market premiums have been 7% lower than in states that have not.

Legislation I introduced to combat the #opioid epidemic and hold drug manufacturers accountable for negligent & misleading distribution practices passed the Senate earlier this month. This week, that legislation was signed into law.

Congressional Republicans have tried at least 70 times to repeal the Affordable Care Act since it was passed. These plans would cut #Medicaid & kick more than 20 million Americans off of health coverage over the next decade.

We must #ProtectOurCare.
My heart goes out to the victims and families of this unspeakable violence. There's no place in our country for violence. Thank you to all of the first responders for their heroic and quick actions.

I supported the #Medicare improvements in the Affordable Care Act, which added years of solvency to the Medicare hospital trust fund and began to close the prescription drug donut hole, saving seniors on out-of-pocket drug costs. #ProtectOurCare

We’re not doing a good enough job tracking the distribution of #opioids. Legislation I wrote was signed into law this week and introduces stiffer fines & penalties for those who don’t do their job in tracking the distribution of these drugs.

The Affordable Care Act preserves every cent of Medicare-guaranteed benefits and makes improvements to the program.

The #ACA included improvements and delivery system reforms that are strengthening and improving #Medicare.
The Affordable Care Act allows #Medicare patients to get preventive services like cancer screenings and annual physicals without a co-pay. This helps about 785,000 Washington seniors. #ProtectOurCare

Nearly 650 Washingtonians & 50,000 Americans died of an #opioid or heroin overdose in 2017 alone.

That’s why I’ve worked with people from Port Angeles to Spokane, Vancouver to Everett, to provide resources that our law enforcement & communities need to tackle this crisis.
Because of important changes included in the Affordable Care Act, Washington seniors covered by #Medicare have saved an average of $978. We must #ProtectOurCare.
President Trump’s budget request for fiscal year 2019 included more than $1.4 trillion in #Medicaid cuts. We must #ProtectOurCare and defend patients in Washington state.

Make no mistake: If the provision of the #ACA that protects Americans with pre-existing conditions is struck down, it would lead to more chaos. Millions of people would be at risk of discrimination or denial of #healthcare coverage.

Americans want more affordable #healthcare with meaningful coverage—not junk plans that don’t protect us.

The Trump administration is pushing yet another plan to expand junk insurance that doesn’t cover basics & hurts people with pre-existing conditions.

https://t.co/Rqdpq7sk6V

Large quantities of #opioids have flooded our communities because of excessive shipments from manufacturers. In our state, a physician in Everett wrote more than 10,000 prescriptions of opioids—26 times higher than the average prescriber in Everett.

In #Aberdeen yesterday, I met with law enforcement officials and local leaders to discuss new resources I authored to fight the #opioid epidemic. This new law is good news for Washingtonians across the Olympic Peninsula.

Today, on #VeteransDay, we celebrate and honor the bravery, courage, and sacrifice shown by the women and men who served in the United States Armed Forces, who protected and strengthened our democratic values.

Our veterans strengthen our communities with their bravery, knowledge & dedication. As we reflect & celebrate the unwavering courage of our veterans, we must continue to fulfill the promises we have made to those who sacrificed so much to uphold our values & protect our freedoms.

Today, the @SIHB1 unveiled a new report on the prevalence of missing and murdered indigenous women and girls in the United States.

This report is evidence that this problem is more than real—it’s horrifying. We need to do more.

Read more here: https://t.co/p81oFdzrkV https://t.co/HVYPIqwqOG

After months of negotiations, today we secured a #bipartisan agreement to pass the Coast Guard reauthorization bill. This bill is a win for Washington state, improving oversight of oil spill risks and protecting Washington state waters from invasive species.

I am proud to cosponsor Savanna’s Act, which would require better reporting of violence against Native women. Every community needs these tools.

Today the @IndianCommittee passed this legislation, which we need to put on the president’s desk before the end of the year.

In the @USCG legislation passed today, I secured a waiver to protect Washington state shipyard jobs at Dakota Creek Industries in Anacortes. This would allow the newly-built America’s Finest vessel to finally fish in American waters.
I am committed to ensuring rural communities have access to the #healthcare they need. #RuralHealth https://t.co/x54VZLm5jY

A report released by @TheUIHI found at least 506 cases of missing or murdered Native women & girls in 71 urban areas across the country, with Seattle & Tacoma home to the highest number of cases.

These findings are a wake-up call that must be answered. #MMIWG https://t.co/NzOgS4hc4x
The #USCG reauthorization bill passed yesterday includes important science-based updates that will benefit Washington state #fishermen and help protect Washington’s coasts and waterways.
Getting additional resources to rural and low-income communities is crucial to solving our nation’s most pressing #healthcare challenges. #RuralHealth

The #PolarStar icebreaker, homeported in Seattle, plays a key role in allowing the @USCG to conduct its mission requirements in the Polar regions & protect our interests in the Arctic.

Legislation passed yesterday authorizes the recapitalization of this Coast Guard #icebreaker.
On #RuralHealthDay, I'm proud to have co-sponsored legislation to increase access to high-quality #healthcare in rural America—where it can be difficult to access a specialist.
I was proud to vote for the #CoastGuard legislation that passed in the Senate yesterday, strengthening paid family leave policies for @USCG members and their families. #PFL

Washington state is rich in #maritime history & heritage, and the #CoastGuard is a large part of that.

This week’s bill includes many provisions important to our @USCG, our environment & to our shipbuilding community. It represents a true, bipartisan effort to find solutions.
